2ï¸âƒ£ INTERVIEW EXPLANATION (ENGLISH)
ğŸ”¹ Short (30 sec)

â€œThis project estimates the speed of vehicles from video footage.
YOLOv8 is used for object detection, a centroid-based tracking algorithm maintains object identity across frames, and speed is calculated using frame-to-frame displacement and FPS-based time conversion.â€

ğŸ”¹ Detailed (1â€“2 min)

â€œThe system processes video frames using OpenCV.
YOLOv8 detects vehicles in each frame and outputs bounding boxes.
A custom centroid-based tracking algorithm assigns unique IDs by comparing Euclidean distance between object centers across frames.
The displacement of each object is calculated and divided by the time difference derived from FPS to estimate speed, which is finally converted to km/h.â€